# Universal standards

Apply in every repository. Complements stack-specific rules in `frontend.mdc` / `backend.mdc` and repo-specific rules.

## Git workflow

- Before starting work, check for uncommitted changes; if any exist, commit them first using Conventional Commits.
- Commit completed work at the end of a task.
- **Conventional Commits:** `type(scope): description` — types: `feat`, `fix`, `refactor`, `chore`, `test`, `docs`, `style`.
- Commit messages: English, imperative mood, no trailing period.

## Code quality

- **TypeScript:** Never use `any`. Use explicit types or `unknown` with narrowing.
- Do not use deprecated APIs or library features; verify in docs when unsure.
- Keep files small and focused; if a file grows past ~200 lines, consider splitting.
- Start every file with a brief top-of-file comment describing its purpose.
- Non-obvious logic needs inline comments explaining **why**, not what the code literally does.

## Testing

- Every feature must include tests.
- When changing or removing behavior, update or remove the corresponding tests.
- All tests must pass before committing.

## Accessibility (UI work)

- Interactive elements need proper ARIA labels or roles.
- Images need meaningful `alt` text.
- Keyboard navigation must work for all interactive components.
- Color contrast meets **WCAG AA**.
- Prefer semantic HTML (`button`, `nav`, `main`, `section`, …); never use a `div` as a clickable control.
